This product builds on ideas from:
  - Matt Pocock's skills (https://github.com/mattpocock/skills),
    in particular `ubiquitous-language` and `improve-codebase-architecture`.
    Reference talk: "Software Fundamentals Matter More Than Ever".
  - Mario Zechner's pi-mono (https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono).
    Pi-mono is the harness pattern this Go port is built against.
  - John Ousterhout, "A Philosophy of Software Design".
  - Eric Evans, "Domain-Driven Design".

The Banks-style ship-name pack draws aesthetic inspiration from
the Culture novels of Iain M. Banks. The Oblique Strategy card pack
draws inspiration from Brian Eno and Peter Schmidt's Oblique
Strategies. Neither is endorsed by the respective rights holders.
